    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-04-10T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-04-10T14:00:00-05:00" n="210"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d210">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1100 CO/4–1053-Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Deputy United States High Commissioner for Germany
                            (<persName type="from">Reber</persName>) to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d210fn1">Also sent <gloss target="#t_niact1">NIACT</gloss>
                        to Munich; repeated to Vienna, Belgrade, Athens, Rome, and Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonn</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-04-10T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 10, 1953—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4562. Following is the tentative itinerary for Roy Cohn, Chief Counsel, and
                    George David Schine, Chief Consultant, staff members Senate Committee on
                    Government Operations.</p>
                <list>
                    <item>Munich–Vienna April 10 PA 180 leave 1235 arrive 1400.</item>
                    <item>Vienna–Munich April 12 PA 181 leave 1515 arrive 1640.</item>
                    <item>Munich–Belgrade April 14 YU 241 leave 1210 arrive 1625.</item>
                    <item>Belgrade–Athens April 16 YU 410 leave 0800 arrive 1305.</item>
                    <item>Athens–Rome April 17 BE 127 leave 1255 arrive 1605.</item>
                    <item>Rome–Paris blank Paris–States blank.</item>
                </list>
                <p>The above staff members have specifically requested that all information
                    regarding the following be referred to them for reply.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>(a)</label>
                    <item>Itinerary.</item>
                    <label>(b)</label>
                    <item>Individuals and subjects discussed with them.</item>
                </list>
                <p>Under no circumstances are any of the posts to set up any schedules prior to
                    consulting with Cohn and Schine.</p>
                <p>Meet and hotel at each post. Notify onward post of ETA and ETD.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reber</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
